Nike celebrated the 35th Anniversary of the Nike Dunk by releasing the Nike Dunk Low SP Syracuse (2020), now available on StockX. The Nike Dunk debuted as part of the 1985 Nike College Colorï¿½s program, a program that delivered footwear in the school colors of 12 popular basketball programs allowing fans to support their favorite teams from head to toe. This Syracuse colorway was among the first collegiate colorways Nike released, breaking the mold for colorways used on basketball shoes.

This Nike Dunk Low SP is composed of a white leather upper with orange blaze leather overlays. A white midsole, orange outsole, and classic Nike branding on the tongue complete the design. These sneakers released in March of 2020 and retailed for $100.
